In [26]:
n_each=above_six.groupby(['quality','color']).count()['alcohol']
n_color=above_six.groupby('color').count()['alcohol']
ratio = n_each / n_color
ratio.plot(kind='bar' , color=['red','blue'] , title='Proportion by Wine Color and Quality');

-white wine is more likely to be higher in quality

conclusion:¶

the main characteristics that keep wine quality above 6 are to stay in these ranges :

-range of chlorides is [ .01 : .12 ]

-range of density is [  .989 :  .998 ]

-range of alcohol is [10.2 : 11.9]

-range of residual sugar is [1:10]

-range of PH is [3.1 : 3.4]

-range of total sulfur dioxide is [1:15]

-range of free sulfur dioxide is [20:65]
